caption: Brunch and the setting here is better than most. I like it here, excellent food & service. I'll return with my relatives. It has a nice interior. Food is like a restaurant in Jacksonville I loved.
Great spot for brunch. I think I might become a regular. Prices were fair for the quality of the food.
BLT was perfect!
Lovely part of downtown

Nestled in the heart of downtown Baltimore, Werner's is a local institution, serving a who's who of breakfast and lunch patrons. Once a film set for the "House of Cards" Netflix series, the atmosphere is reminiscent of an old diner. There are no bad choices on the menu, with an array of salads, sandwiches, and Greek food. Werner's doesn't accept reservations, and you won't be seated until all members of your party are present.

This diner is located somewhat on a backstreet, but worth seeking out if your in the inner harbor area. The best breakfast place in the neighborhood that I found, although they do not open until 8 am unfortunately. If you like nostalgia and interior design it’s a must visit for the beautiful late 40:s and 50:s interior, well preserved. Good food. Good service. Reasonable prices. Simple menu. Nice staff. Cool space in a neat old building.
rude and mean cash register she treated me with racism and disrespectful because I am forign
Nicest place for breakfast.
Good food
Good food, but you can't substitute any food items on the lunch special menu and they are a bit  pricey.

Love it here. Very friendly service was quick and theh helped me and my friend out when we needed it the most. Very hot day, and I had my dog. It's not a pet friendly place, but they allowed my German sheperd to come in and gave her some water, we bought something to drink and it was so relaxing. Clean, and quiet place to eat. Recommended to go and try out.
Super fast service, very friendly staff, and good food. Perfect for a quick bite during jury duty lunch break. Big portions and fair prices.
A great little hole-in-the-wall lunch the food was amazing and so are the waitresses
Always a good lunch. Recommend the Gyro with fries.

If I could rate them a 0 I would. The food is terrible and the food is over priced for what you get. I have tried them on two other occasions and wasnt happy. This is my third time and I won't be returning. I ordered a simple hamburger, cooked well done with fries. I got a burger that was burned not char but burned so black that  I  had to scrape off the burn.  The fries were salty but I am noticing that everything they make is salty. Whomever the cook is, they are obviously unhappy or lack culinary skills for food preparation. I will not be returning. Worst food in downtown Baltimore Ever!!!!
Great food! Love the historic appeal. Check out all the movie posters! This was a part of the show the Wire!

This is a gem! Best French Toast I've had in a while. The interior design is very historic, but in a tasteful manner. I forsee having cravings in the future when I'm home in NYC and hopping on a bus just for their French toast.
Had a Turkey club that was so huge it was like 2 large sandwiches
Slow service
This is a fantastic diner. Retro interior. Great food wonderful service.

Great staff. Fast service. Try a cup of the "half and half" soup (cream of crab and Maryland crab) as an appetizer. Plenty of standard dinner fare and lots of good Greek selections. They also make egg creams if you're into that.
Great breakfast and lunches. Hidden gem. Not open weekends, though. Hours 8-3 can be limiting.
30 minutes to get my breakfast?!!!  Not what I expected from a luncheonette.
My veggie burger & sweet potato fries were delicious!

How did I not know about this place until today?? Adorable, old fashioned diner so close to the harbor and downtown offices. Had a fantastic turkey reuben "the rachel" today. Great service. Put it on your list.
Great old-school eatery with good food and very friendly service.

Maybe I'm just used to the quality of food in NJ, but this place was hot trash to me. I first had a hair in my orange juice, when I addressed it, she just brushed it off like it wasn't a big thing. Corn beef was crunchy, I didn't get my home fries at first because she thought I wanted fruit instead (I said fruit on the side) when she came back with the home fries I thought she left some in the back.  My stomach is full so there's that, but it wasn't worth the 12 dollars that I paid.
I had the crab soup and it was great.
"The Alex Brown Cafeteria"
Good sandwiches great place for lunch
Nice quaint diner with a really menu and pocket friendly. Definitely will return.
Great dinner food
I was expecting a fruit compote with the fruit pancakes but I ended up with green apples made in pancakes like who even eats that
A hidden gem and a slice of history nestled into the business district of downtown Baltimore. Solid basic food. Solid service. Amazing atmosphere.

Great place for lunch in under an hour for all the businesses in this area.  Huge variety of food from chicken tenders to quesadillas to spinach pie to cheesesteaks to a great selection of salads. The salmon is just to die for. Love all of the staff, from the cooks and servers to the management and the owner himself!  Great set up. And they truly know and understand the meaning of fast yet excellent service. Their food absolutely never disappoints.  Been a faithful regular for almost 7 years and I seem to love it more and more with each year that passes!

Great, I said great, breakfast, but don't miss lunch! Fridays special was a shrimp salad roll. Awesome and I think there was crab meat in there. My Financé had a huge club sandwich. Just right bread and meat. Really nice people work this place, not "staff'" but really Baltimore friendly people. Classic booth and counter seating. I like it!
We went there in the early morning. Service took a bit, but the food ended up being good.
Expensive but got a turkey BLT and it was great.
Great prices, great amount of good food and great service!
I love this old restaurant and the simple, honest food it sells.
What a great place to eat lunch. A slice of history from the early 50s. Go.
Salad too sweet.  Service is good.
Great food and amazing atmosphere. This country needs more places like this.
Great tasting food. The place is a little small, so if you are going to lunch with a large crowd, you should probably call. Would definitely go back.

I Truly would not recommend this place. There were less than 10 people in the restaurant and it took more then 30 minutes to bring out a breakfast.  Scrambled eggs with 2 slices of cheese layed on them pancakes that were semi warm with Hard butter and scrapple that they said took 15 minutes to cook was 1/16 of an inch thick. This was THE WORST BREAKFAST EVER....... DENNY'S IS BETTER. The managers John attitude was most unpleasant, Justin the server was slow and very Bad.
Okay but too crowded
Stopped here about 10 yrs ago for a quick cheeseburger for lunch...oh so good :)

Expensive! Although the Staff was not very welcoming to me, they had no problem taking my $$$. Used to visit in the 80's and planned to visit more often than not, going forward. Fortunately, I am choosing the latter.
Great lunch stop.  Gyro was well prepared with quality ingredients.

An expansive menu with a handful of vegetarian options. The food is good and the prices are cheap. Very retro diner vibe. The service is prompt and friendly, I have never had to wait for a table or had to wait more than 10 minutes for my food. Great place to go if you are just visiting because it is "Baltimore famous" with scenes from The Wire and House of Cards filmed there.
Great food and service.
Authentic, nice old style feel
Old school in midtown
The restaurant experience was very good.  They have an intersting menu.  The service was very good.
Really great service and delicious deli American subs. Their chicken noodle soup was sooo good! A cute 1930’s style dinner
Nice, historic diner.  Good food, good service, good prices.

Werners is a locals favorite for lunch. People that work nearby fill this place up at lunchtime. They aren't open for dinner. This place has become a stop for tourists because it has been a location used in several House of Cards episodes. Nothing fancy to see here. Just good lunch food.
Alright food, and a bit on the expensive side.
Good old fashion diner. Seriously like you walked into the 1950s. Great breakfast,  $6.50 for 4 pieces of bacon, 2 eggs, homefries and toast.
Local, down to earth affordable with quality food

This is now a real diner, though it doesn't look like one; it's a cute, cozy old wooden-booth nook in an old office building. The current owner is from a real NJ Greek diner family, and the precision and quality show; he's helped by a loyal staff of veteran servers. It's much better than in years past.  There's a rush hour of freed cubicle-dwellers 11:50-12:50, so go before or after for you milkshake and club sandwich. Zero parking.

The staff is super friendly and fast. The food is pretty on point. I have consistently gotten good service and my food has been delicious every time. I generally order breakfast, but on the occasions that I have gotten lunch, I've been pleased just the same.
Great Greek food. A lot of movies and shows filmed here.
Food is great here! Love the grilled cheese. Nothing special or fancy. Just well made food.
Popular place for lunch, avoid the rush if possible by going before noon or after 1 pm
Good old fashioned diner, great breakfast, good prices

This is a classic downtown breakfast / lunch spot with wood panels. They serve the usual  fare like breakfast platters, sandwiches and salads. Feels like the set of a movie from the 1950’s. At popular times the service can be slow.
OldSchool Diner, Great food and service...
Great food,  fast service.

Good, quick breakfast. The previous reviewer caused a run on eggs benedict ("I don't know why, but everyone's been ordering it this week! ") so they didn't have any Canadian bacon left, but I had it with normal bacon. Still good!  Very classic wood-paneled ambiance.
Came in as they opened... This place is old school (and not in a hipster way) classic booths, killer Eggs Benedict & the coffee was hot. Nothing fancy, just what you need!
Try the traditional American sandwiches instead of the Greek food.
Great place for lunch in the Business District.  Vast menu, and the people try to please.  They are open for breakfast too, and it is wonderful unpretentious work discussion.  The food is very good.
One of my favorite restaurants in Baltimore. Old-school lunch counter food -- try the spanakopita or the greek salad.

Owner/Manger is arrogant. When approached about an entire order for a 3 top being incorrect... he proceeded to provide reasoning and excuses.  People go there on their lunch break. They have limited time so accuracy is key.  The organization of their workflow is horrible.   Everyone is running around and trying to get things done. They always look like they are behind. PICKLES...are not included on a hamburger nor do they advise you of the upcharge. HOWEVER... hots are included on a burger and there is no upcharge.    IF there is an upcharge for any items.. it is the servers obligation to tell the customer.  Wont be going back to this establishment anymore!! I can find a cheeseburger anywhere.
Classic Baltimore.
